subSubSection.paragraph:
As correctly reported by 
Chemsak & Hovore (2002b)
for this species “the variation within and be- tween samples is considerable.” The elytral pubescence (
Figs. 101, 106-109
) is extremely variable in concentration, but much less so in position of the maculae, and although the anterior light pubescent macula of the elytra is from slightly distinct to well-marked its placement on the elytra remains the same.
